20
(2) IC 36-7.6-1-8.
(j) As used in this article, "responsible officer of an audited entity"
refers to the chief executive officer or another individual who has
executive decision making authority for the audited entity with respect
to a compliance obligation prescribed by or established under this
article or another law.
SECTION 20. IC 5-16-15-5, AS ADDED BY P.L.149-2021,
