Sec. 77. "Community intellectual disability and other
developmental disabilities centers", for purposes of IC 12-29
(except as provided in IC 12-29-3-6), means a program of services
that meets the following conditions:
(1) Is approved by the division of disability, aging, and
rehabilitative services.
(2) Is organized for the purpose of providing multiple services
for persons with developmental disabilities.
(3) Is operated by one (1) of the following or any combination
of the following:
(A) A city, a town, a county, or another political
subdivision of Indiana.
(B) An agency of the state.
(C) An agency of the United States.
(D) A political subdivision of another state.
(E) A hospital owned or operated by a unit of government
described in clauses (A) through (D).
