SECTION 169. IC 31-19-7-1, AS AMENDED BY P.L.128-2012,
SECTION 48, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1. (a) A child may not be placed in a proposed
adoptive home without the prior written approval of a licensed child
placing agency or the local office approved for that purpose by the
department.
(b) Except as provided in subsection (d), before giving prior written
approval for placement in a proposed adoptive home of a child, a
