indirectly, provides:
(A) services to a child or family of a child, for which payment
is made, in whole or in part, by the department of child
services or a local office of the department of child services;
(B) services to:
(i) a child who is; or
(ii) a family with;
a child at imminent risk of placement (as defined in
IC 31-26-5-1) who is referred by the department of child
services or a local office of the department of child services to
the person for family support or family preservation services;
or
(C) assistance to or works in cooperation with the department
